Title: Object: Ex aegypto vocavi filium meum (I called my son out of Egypt)
Description: The Virgin sitting on a rock at the foot of a small tree, her left arm around the child Jesus, who leans across her to berries which St Joseph brings in a fold of his cloak, standing on the left; after Maratta; lettered state, with number (erased on this impression). 1760 Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: The date is taken from Calabi + de Vesme.
Bibliographic references: Calabi & De Vesme 1928 / Francesco Bartolozzi. Catalogue des estampes et notice biographique d'après les manuscrits de A. De Vesme entièrement réformés et complétés d'une étude critique par A. Calabi (94.II)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (CMC in Philipe's hand on the verso in oval blindstamp)
